## PHASE 3.4: Handle Standalone Recipe Data

### A. Update RecipeDetailView for Standalone Recipes

**Standalone recipes have different data structure:**

| Data | Puzzle Recipe | Standalone Recipe |
|------|---|---|
| Components | 4 (crust/cream/filling/decor) | None |
| Instructions | From recipe_instruction_steps (4 separate) | From instructions field (single text) |
| Cooking Steps | 4 blocks (one per component) | Single instruction block |

**Update RecipeDetailView logic:**

```typescript
const isSingleInstruction = recipe.is_standalone;

if (isSingleInstruction) {
  // Standalone: show as single instruction block
  const steps = recipe.instructions
    .split('\n')
    .filter(s => s.trim())
    .map((s, i) => ({
      step_number: i + 1,
      step_description: s.trim(),
      // No base_recipe_id, ingredients, equipment for simple
    }));

  return <CookingMode steps={steps} recipe={recipe} />;
} else {
  // Puzzle: show 4 component blocks (current logic)
  // ... existing code
}
```

